    "Finally, for JPEG Pleno, subjects are more inclined to choose P1 or P2 over P3, suggesting that, to obtain higher visual quality, it is preferable to allocate a similar or a higher bitrate to the color when compared to the geometry.The reconstructed JOD values are reported in Fig. 13 against the bitrate.",
    "As underlined in Sect. 6, the displayed JOD values only reflect relationships between the subjective Fig.",
    "13 Reconstructed JOD values against the bitrate for each image and codec quality of point clouds compressed with the same codec and rate, i.e., it is not possible to derive the number of JOD between stimuli at different rates.",
    "The plots in Fig. 13 highlight the points that can be compared in terms of JOD by connecting them with lightgrey lines.",
    "The conclusions derived from these plots are similar to what can be observed from Table 7, but additional nuances regarding the influence of the content and rate can also be observed."
